Global investors  bought a  net 6.24
billion rupees ($116 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, declined 29.8 percent to 751.6 billion rupees on
the last day of trading in contracts for October, according to
the exchangeâ€™s  website . Open interest reached a record 1.6
trillion rupees on Sept. 21, 2010.  Foreign funds sold a net 5.51 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data given
